Detailed Description

cvmx_pow_wq_int_thr#

Contains the thresholds for enabling and setting work queue interrupts. For more information regarding this register, see the interrupt section. Note: Up to 4 of the POW's internal storage buffers can be allocated for hardware use and are therefore not available for incoming work queue entries. Additionally, any PP that is not in the NULL_NULL state consumes a buffer. Thus in a 4 PP system, it is not advisable to set either IQ_THR or DS_THR to greater than 512 - 4 - 4 = 504. Doing so may prevent the interrupt from ever triggering.
